<div>New Bathroom Products Address Safety, Comfort and Green Concerns</div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
<div>
  <div><a href="http://www.nbnnews.com/NBN/issues/2011-06-27/Building+Products/index.html#" target="_self"><img name="" src="http://www.nbnnews.com/NBN/version3/editor_images/june27_NuTone240.jpg" alt="photo" border="0" width="240"></a></div>
  <p>The bathroom may be the “necessary room,” but that   doesn’t mean it has to be one-dimensional. These products from member of   NAHB’s <a href="http://www.nahb.org/page.aspx/category/sectionID=469/fromGSA=1" target="_blank">Leading Suppliers Council</a> address safety, comfort and green concerns, and they do it with style.</p>
  <p><strong>Love the Blues</strong></p>
  <p>Anyone who’s ever headed for a bathroom in the middle of the night   has experienced that no-win choice: stumble through the darkness, or   turn on a light and squint through momentary blindness. </p>
  <p><a href="http://www.nutone.com/" target="_blank">NuTone</a>'s new   LunAura ventilation fan/light combination makes it easy to turn on the   light. While its ceiling light provides bright task lighting during the   day, the nighttime setting provides soft, blue LED light that   illuminates the entire room at a level of brightness suggestive of a   twilight sky.  </p>
  <p>This <a href="http://www.energystar.gov/" target="_blank">Energy Star</a>-qualified product provides quiet, powerful ventilation — 110 CFM at 0.7 Sones — and comes in three contemporary styles.</p>
  <p><strong>A Talented Toilet</strong></p>
  <p>These days, toilets need to multi-task. They need to work reliably,   look nice, be comfortable to use and do their bit to save the planet by   not wasting water.</p>
