  <a href="http://www.gerberonline.com/default.aspx" target="_blank">Gerber ’s</a> Avalanche gravity-fed model does all that, with understated grace.
  <p>It uses only 1.28 gallons of water per flush, compared to the   industry’s standard of 1.6 gallons, saving up to 8,760 gallons of water   every year.</p>
  <p>Its dual-fed siphon jet is larger than what’s found in most conventional models, for more effective and reliable functionality. </p>
  <p>The toilet comes with an elongated bowl as well as a standard   configuration, and is available in a somewhat taller “ErgoHeight”   version that makes it easier for those with mobility issues to use.</p>
  <p>The design is simple and straightforward, working with any decor, and the <a href="http://www.gerberonline.com/downloads/productliterature/fixtures/avalanche.pdf" target="_blank">Avalanche</a> comes in white, bone and biscuit. </p>
