  <p>More Green Trends:</p>
  <p><strong>Burgeoning Trends</strong></p>
  <p>One of the most popular home technology systems   that builders currently are installing is lighting control.   Many consumers are more aware of this measurable part of their budgets.   They can forsee the benefits and are willing to make the investment.</p>
  <p>This trend to continue as more home owners attempt to reduce their household costs. </p>
  <p>Another technology frequently requested is   “daylight harvesting” — using an astronomical clock or similar   programming to operate motorized window shades. Properly used window   shades can save home owners a significant portion of their energy   consumption.</p>
  <p>In the summertime, shades passively cool the home,   and in the winter they are programmed to allow optimum daylight to   enter and warm the home.</p>
  <p>Energy dashboards and energy management are also a   burgeoning trend. This allows the home owner to actively   monitor the amount of energy used by way of a dashboard that visually   indicates the energy levels in the home.</p>
  <p>Programming options allow home owners to monitor their home’s energy output and adjust their consumption.</p>
  <p>Solar energy is another popular system in specific regions that is increasing in demand.</p>
